ABSOLUTE TALENT RULES:
- If a talent reference is provided, YOU MUST use that exact person.
- Facial identity, body proportions, and physical presence are locked.
- No beautification, no identity blending, no age shift.
- Skin texture must remain natural, editorial-grade.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
GARMENT CONSTRAINTS (HYPER-BINDING)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The garment is the CORE NARRATIVE DRIVER of the cover.

You MUST preserve:
- exact garment design
- silhouette, proportions, and fit
- material behavior and texture
- construction logic and fashion intent

You are NOT allowed to:
- redesign or reinterpret the garment
- neutralize its attitude
- flatten its visual impact

The COVER MOOD, COLOR, and ENERGY must be derived from this garment.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
COVER CONCEPT & CREATIVE DIRECTION
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

This image is a MAGAZINE COVER.

It MUST:
- feel bold and intentional
- feature a strong pose or gesture
- include dynamic body language
- show attitude, tension, or provocation
- never feel static, passive, or neutral

Creative direction principles:
- asymmetry is encouraged
- strong graphic balance
- fashion as statement, not documentation
- controlled chaos is allowed if fashion-driven

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
POSE, GESTURE & PRESENCE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Pose:
- Strong, expressive, fashion-forward
- Twists, bends, steps, crouches, or angular stances are encouraged
- Body must interact with space and framing

Expression:
- Assertive, defiant, playful, or enigmatic
- Direct gaze OR intentional off-camera tension
- Emotional clarity, not neutrality

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
COLOR & MOOD (GARMENT-DRIVEN)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

- The overall color direction MUST be derived from the garment
- Background color may contrast or amplify the outfit
- Bold, editorial color fields are encouraged

Mood examples (choose based on garment):
- power
- rebellion
- elegance
- modern sensuality
- fearless confidence

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PHOTOGRAPHY & CAMERA LANGUAGE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

You are shooting with a TOP HIGH-FASHION PHOTOGRAPHER mindset.

Allowed photographic characteristics:
- professional full-frame or medium-format look
- framing intentionally random but editorially precise
- unexpected crops or negative space
- slight motion blur where it adds energy
- intentional lens flare when physically plausible
- high or pushed exposure if fashion-driven

Film & texture:
- visible editorial film grain
- no digital smoothness
- texture adds character, not noise

FOCUS RULE:
- The model AND the garment must always be in clear visual focus
- Effects must NEVER obscure fashion readability

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
MAGAZINE COVER GRAPHICS (MANDATORY)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The cover MUST include:

- A large, recognizable fashion magazine logo at the top (e.g. ELLE-style masthead)
- Editorial headlines and cover lines placed around the subject
- Typography must feel realistic, professional, and fashion-editorial

Text rules:
- Text must be readable
- No brand advertising
- No product slogans
- Editorial language only (fashion, culture, style)

Examples of cover lines:
- A main feature headline (bold, confident)
- Secondary editorial teasers
- Issue or seasonal reference

Typography must integrate with:
- pose
- composition
- negative space
- subject overlap where appropriate

